            <h1>Shortbread Biscuit Recipe</h1>
            
            <p> The easiest 3 step shortbread biscuit recipe. They're wonderfully <br> <b>crumbly</b> and delicious and will melt in your mouth.
                Here is a step by step guide to create the best biscuits.
            </p>
            
            <a href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=TtTYnTKEQN8" target="_blank"> A visual video tutorial</a>
            
            <br> <img src="Shortbread biscuit.jpg" alt="image of a shortbread" Width="20%">
            
            <div>
            
                <h3>Ingredients:</h3>
        
                <ul>
                    <li>1 cup of unsalted butter (softened)</li>
                    <li>1/2 cup sugar</li>
                    <li>2 cups all purpose flour</li>
                </ul>
    
                <h3>Instructions:</h3>
                <ol>
                    <li>Pre-heat your oven to 350c.</li>
                    <li>Prepare two large baking sheets lined with parchment paper</li>
                    <li>In a large bowl, cream together butter and sugar.</li>
                    <li>Add flour and continue to mix until mixture forms a soft dough</li>
                    <li>Form dough into a cohesive ball with your hands.</li>
                    <li>Roll dough 1/4-inch thick on a surface dusted with flour.</li>
                    <li>Use your desired cookie cutters and place onto baking sheets.
                    <li>Bake for 16-18 minutes, or until cookies are pale golden brown. 
                        Let cool on baking sheets.</li>
                    <li>Finally, Enjoy!</li>
                </ol>
            </div>
    
